    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1934-04-11T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1934-04-11T00:00:00-05:00" n="438"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d438">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">868.51 War Credits/661</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the Greek
                        Minister</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Simopoulos</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1934-04-11">April 11,
                            1934</date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: I refer to your Note No. 995, dated March 29,
                    1934, in which you notified the Government of the United States that on account
                    of present difficulties the Greek Government is compelled to postpone, in
                    accordance with the option granted under Clause 2 of Part 1 of the debt funding
                    agreement of May 10, 1929, the payment of bond No. 13, dated January 1, 1928,
                    maturing July 1, 1934, in the principal amount of $150,000.</p>
                <p>I am requested by the Secretary of the Treasury to advise you that the United
                    States takes notice of the action of your Government in this connection, and
                    also to advise you that, in accordance with the terms of the agreement, the
                    postponement is for a period of six months from July 1, 1934.</p>
                <p>Accept [etc.]</p>
                <closer>For the Secretary of State:<lb/>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">William Phillips</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
